(Might want to check the repository, if these is something newer or whatever)
sudo add-apt-repository -y ppa:neovim-ppa/unstable
sudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get install -y neovim
pip install --user neovim

Maybe update pip for good measure: pip install --upgrade pip


make the dir:
~/.config/nvim/  

and create a file called

init.vim 

then make a symbolic link between
that one and ~/.vimrc(Thank god), like so: 

ln -s ~/.vimrc ~/.config/nvim/init.vim


